# Style guide — colors and typography

Text and UI across all pages must use **only** the following.

## Colors

Use only design tokens from the style guide (see `/style-guide`):

- **Background / foreground**: `bg-background`, `text-foreground`, `text-background`
- **Semantic palette**: `text-muted`, `text-subtle`, `text-accent`, `border-border`, `border-border-strong`, `bg-surface`, `bg-surface-hover`, etc.

Do **not** use Tailwind default colors (e.g. `zinc-*`, `gray-*`, `text-black`, `bg-white`) or arbitrary hex/rgb.

## Typography

Use only the typography utility classes defined in `src/app/globals.css`:

- `.text-button` — buttons, nav links (Neue Montreal, 12px, line-height 14px)
- `.text-section` — section headings (Departure Mono, 12px, line-height 18px, uppercase)
- `.text-body` — body text (Neue Montreal, 16px, line-height 22px)
- `.text-display` — hero headline (Neue Montreal, 28px, line-height 34px, white)

Do **not** use raw Tailwind text sizes (e.g. `text-sm`, `text-lg`, `text-xl`, `text-2xl`) for content. Combine typography classes with color tokens: e.g. `text-body text-gray-blue`, `text-section text-foreground`.

Font families: use `font-sans` (Neue Montreal) or `font-mono` (Departure Mono) only when needed in addition to a `.text-*` typography class (those classes already set font-family).
